Model 6 - Leaps Package
The Leaps package is an â€œregression subset selectionâ€ tool. The package automatically generates
all possible models. The tool is basically used to find the â€œbestâ€ model. This tool will be
compared to another (further down below). According to the documentation, the algorithm
within leaps returns a best â€œmodel of each sizeâ€.
After running the package, I inputed the â€œbestâ€ model mannualy in R, as to not have to rerun
each time. The below output shows the results of that model.
