Model 7- glmulti Package
The glmulti package is an â€œautomated model selection and model averagingâ€ tool. The package
automatically generates all possible models â€œwith the specified response and explanatory
variablesâ€. The tool is basically used to find the â€œbestâ€ model. The library/function itself took
over 10 minutes for my PC to run - since it was set to use an exhaustive approach to selecting the
best model.
After running the package, I inputed the â€œbestâ€ model mannualy in R, as to not have to rerun
(10+ mins) each time.
The glmulti package is designed to handle binary logistic regression.
